Two young people were shot dead and 19 others, including an infant, injured after gunmen sprayed bullets into a crowd at an outdoor barbecue in Toronto.

The names of victims have not been released, but one was a young teenage girl and the other a 20-year-old man.

Many of those hurt were injured in the panic that ensued after shots were fired in Scarborough, a suburb in east Toronto just before 11pm last night.

