'It is the most serious crime of its kind that has ever taken place in the city of Toronto,' said Police Chief Bill Blair.

Police have made appeals for witnesses to contact them as they began to pull together descriptions for what appeared to be multiple shooters.

A handgun was recovered near the scene, and Mr Blair said one of the injured was considered “a person of interest,' but they are still  looking for other suspects.

